  "prompt": "Will doing organic chemistry from Ncert enough for Neet 17?",
  "response": "Using NCERT textbooks for organic chemistry can be a good strategy for NEET preparation. NCERT books are known for their clear explanations and are aligned with the NEET syllabus. However, to excel in NEET, you may need to supplement your study with additional resources and practice:\n\n1. **NCERT Books:** Thoroughly read and understand all the concepts presented in the NCERT textbooks. Make sure to focus on the exercises and examples given.\n\n2. **Practice Problems:** Regularly solve practice problems and previous years' NEET questions for organic chemistry. This will help you get familiar with the question pattern and difficulty level.\n\n3. **Additional Reference Books:** Consider using other reference books like \"Organic Chemistry\" by Morrison and Boyd, or \"Organic Chemistry\" by MS Chauhan for more advanced problems and detailed explanations.\n\n4. **Mock Tests:** Take mock tests to simulate the exam environment and improve your time management skills. Analyze your performance in these tests to identify and work on your weaknesses.\n\n5. **Online Resources:** Utilize online resources like educational websites, video lectures, and question banks to gain a diverse understanding of the topics.\n\nRemember, while NCERT is a strong foundation, supplementing it with other materials and extensive practice is crucial for scoring well in NEET.",
